<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4661] FileInstall: Property &quot;felix.fileinstall.filter&quot; ignored when the service start</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4661</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the fileinstall service start, it scan the container to find bundles already deployed whose location refers to a file in the configured folder.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this scan ignore the &quot;felix.fileinstall.filter&quot; : a bundle whose location is in the configured folder is registered by the DirectoryWatcher regardless of his name.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for instance, i have a Karaf instance with the following configuration :&lt;br/&gt;
folder: etc, filter: *.cfg, startLevel = 30&lt;br/&gt;
folder: etc, filter: *.xml, startLevel = 80&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if i add a blueprint file in &quot;etc&quot;, it will be transformed into a bundle at location &quot;blueprint:&lt;a href=&quot;file:etc/myfile.xml&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;file:etc/myfile.xml&lt;/a&gt;&quot;. Then, if i restart the container, this bundle will be registered by the two instances of DirectoryWatcher, and nasty things will happen (randomly refresh of this bundle, bundle not starting, etc)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
